article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 63, Bowling Green 60
article.story: MIAMI, Ohio -- Will Felder hit a go-ahead jumper with 2 minutes left and Miami (Ohio) dropped Bowling Green to 0-6 on the road this year in a 63-60 victory Wednesday night. Bowling Green (6-10, 1-2 Mid-American Conference) led the entire game until Felder's jumper tied it 55-55 with 5:23 left. His field goal with 2 minutes remaining gave Miami (7-8, 2-1) its second lead at 61-60. Chauncey Orr's jumper with 2:36 left was the Falcons' last point, with Jordon Crawford missing a jumper and committing two turnovers in Bowling Green's final three possessions. Felder paced Miami with a career-high 20 points on 10-of-14 shooting. Drew McGhee hit 7 of 9 for a season-best 14 points off the bench. The RedHawks came into Wednesday shooting a MAC-best 47.7 percent in conference games, and made 54.9 percent (28 of 51) Wednesday. Bowling Green's Crawford and A'uston Calhoun each scored 21 points.
